title: kuroki_shouzaemon
body:
A character in [[Rakudai Ninja Rantarou]].

Shouzaemon is a 1st year student in Ninjutsu Academy and the class president of the 1st year Ha-class. He shares a room with [[Ninokuruwa Isuke]].

He has a roundly eyes and big triangle eyebrows. His bangs are six thin vertically. In his casual, he wears orange sleeves with dark brown symbol "∩" and purple pants.

title: ninokurowa_isuke
body:
A character in [[Rakudai Ninja Rantarou]].

Isuke is a 1st year student from the Ha-class in Ninjutsu Academy. He is the son of textile dyers, and something of a neat freak. He is often depicted with a broom or mop. He shares a room with [[Kuroki Shouzaemon]].

He has dark brown hair with horizontal hair lines at the end. His bangs and eyebrows are curve. His eyes are dotted with cutted circular lines. In his casual, he has a sky blue sleeves with yellow square lines at the top and blue pants.

title: yumesaki_sanjirou
body:
A character in [[Rakudai Ninja Rantarou]].

Sanjirou is a 1st year student from the Ha-class in Ninjutsu Academy. He enjoys setting traps and shares a room with [[Sasayama Heidayu]], who has the same hobby.

He has small normal eyebrows and eyes are circular doted. His bangs are many small vertical hairs. In his casual, he wears blue sleeves with bird-like shaped and sky blue pants.

title: sasayama_heidayu
body:
A character in [[Rakudai Ninja Rantarou]].

Heidayu is a 1st year student from the Ha-class in Ninjutsu Academy. He likes traps and has his entire room rigged with them. He shares his room with [[Yumesaki Sanjirou]], who also enjoys traps.

He has a oval shaped head, [[blunt bang]]. His eyebrows are brown with sharp edges at the end. He has a small doted eyes with semi circle lines. In his casual, he wears pink sleeves with 3 blue triangles and blue pants.

title: minamoto_kingo
body:
A character in [[Rakudai Ninja Rantarou]].

He is a 1st year student from the Ha-class in Ninjutsu Academy. He is the son of a samurai and his main weapon is katana. He shares a room with [[Yamamura Kisanta]]

Kingo has brown hair with part bangs on the left side, thick eyebrows. His eyes are square and his nose is diamond-shape like. In his casual, He wears light blue sleeves with three black lines and dark blue pants.

title: yamamura_kisanta
body:
A character in [[Rakudai Ninja Rantarou]].

Kisanta is a 1st year student from the Ha-class in Ninjutsu Academy and former student in Fuuma Ninjutsu Academy. He collects slugs as a hobby and shares a room with [[Minamoto Kingo]].

Kisanta has a spiky brown hair, and the bangs are four spiky hairs. His eyes and eyebrows are both curvy. In his casual, he wears a reddish pink sleeves with three yellow squares connect to triangles and dark blue pants.

body:
A character in [[SNK]]'s [[The King of Fighters]] series of games. He wears an eyepatch on his right eye after having lost it to [[Rugal Bernstein]] 8 years before [[The King of Fighters '94]]. Not wanting to be alone, he recruited [[Ralf Jones]] and [[Clark Still]] to form the [[Ikari (game)|Ikari Warriors]] 8 years later.

He has since adopted [[Leona Heidern|Leona]] since [[The King of Fighters '96]], after losing his biological daughter, Clara.

He fights using slashing attacks with his knife glove, a tradition of the Heidern family. He can create a cutting projectile with the glove as well as perform his Stormbringer, one of which he is famous for.

His signature catchphrase is "Go to Hell!" executed during the Final Bringer (since KOF 94) and Heidern's End (only from [[The King of Fighters '98|KOF 98]] through [[The King of Fighters 2001|2001]], he says "The End!" in [[The King of Fighters 2002|KOF 2002: Unlimited Match]] while executing said move).

[spoiler]She is also the actual daughter of 961 President [[Kuroi Takao]]. Neither she nor Kuroi call her Kuroi Shiika due to differences in personality and reputation, but she calls him 'Papa' and he dotes on her.[/spoiler]

title: pixiv_red
body:
Pixiv Red, or Fandom Red, is a depiction of [[red (pokemon)|Red]] that became very popular on Japanese art sharing websites like [[Pixiv]] during the late 2000s to early 2010s. He is a version of the Red that appears on Mt. Silver in [i][[Pokemon HGSS]][/i].

Departing from the game's design, this fandom version had [[short hair|short]], loose [[black hair]] and [[red eyes]] (sometimes [[black eyes|black]], [[brown eyes|brown]], or [[grey eyes|grey]]). He was slim, if not [[toned male|toned]], with a stoic face and a cool persona. His feelings were usually kept very subtle.

 When depicted with a Pokemon, he usually favored [[Charizard]] as his main, or was drawn with [[Pikachu]] as his companion.


[b]Take note:[/b] not every Red depicted as stoic, with black hair, and/or with red eyes is a Pixiv Red. The hair on a typical depiction of Pixiv Red is more relaxed and glossy and does not [[flipped hair|fan out to the sides]], a la post #2278447. His eyes aren't very wide either, compared to his official counterpart.

title: missingno.
body:
Japanese name: [b]けつばん[/b] [i]Ketsuban[/i]

A well-known glitch [[pokemon|Pokémon]] in the [[pokemon_rgby|Generation I games]].

Its typical appearance is a mess of black, purple and orange pixels somewhat resembling a reversed "L" shape. Alternatively, MissingNo. may look like a [[Kabutops]] or [[Aerodactyl]] fossil, like the ones found in the Pewter Museum, or a [[pokemon_tower_ghost|Pokémon Tower ghost]].

It may corrupt the saved game to some extent, including  messing up the trainer image and the Hall of Fame.

Its presence causes the item in the sixth slot to be multiplied. This is sometimes done intentionally by the player, as a method of cheating to have plenty of otherwise very rare or unique items such as [[Master Ball|Master Balls]] and [[Rare Candy|Rare Candies]].

body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park.

The [i]Sivatherium[/i] was the largest giraffid and possibly the largest ruminant known to mankind. It lived around a million years ago and went extinct 8000 years ago (at the latest). Their name means "Shiva's beast", refering to the Hindu god Shiva.

Redesigned Sivatherium has been given many attributes of her namesake: a crescent moon piercing, a "third eye" marking on her hair, a snake scarf, a [[trident|trishula]] and an hourglass-shaped drum. Being extinct, [[empty_eyes|she lacks the shine on her eyes]].

title: evil_dead
body:
[b][i]The Evil Dead[/i][/b] is a 1981 American supernatural horror, gore and comedy film written and directed by "Sam Raimi":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam_Raimi and executive produced by Raimi and "Bruce Campbell":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bruce_Campbel , who also stars alongside Ellen Sandweiss and Betsy Baker. 

Both early and later critical reception were universally positive and in the years since its release, The Evil Dead has developed a reputation as one of the greatest horror films of all time. The movie launched the careers of Campbell and Raimi, who would collaborate on several films together throughout the years, including Raimi's [[Spider-Man]] trilogy.

The film has spawned a media franchise, beginning with two sequels written and directed by Raimi, [i][b]"Evil Dead II":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evil_Dead_II [/b][/i](1987) and [i][b]"Army of Darkness":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Army_of_Darkness [/b][/i](1992), as well as video games, comic books, a musical and a television series. 

The film's protagonist [[Ashley J Williams]] (Campbell) is regarded as a cult movie icon. The fourth film, serving as a reboot, a remake, and a sequel, was titled simply [i][b]"Evil Dead":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evil_Dead_(2013_film)_ [/b][/i] and was released in 2013. 

As with the other films, the follow-up 2015 television series [i][b]"Ash vs Evil Dead":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ash_vs_Evil_Dead [/b][/i]was created and produced by Sam and Ivan Raimi, with Campbell also executive producing.

[[Luciela R. Sourcream]]'s third character class following [[diabla (elsword)|Diabla]]. She is partnered with [[ciel (elsword)|Ciel]]'s [[annuller (elsword)|Annuller]] class.

[i]Iblis[/i] is the Islamic counterpart of Christianity and Judaism's Satan.

title: diabla_(elsword)
body:
One of [[luciela r. sourcream|Lu]]'s character classes, succeeded by [[iblis (elsword)|Iblis]]. Her [[symbol-shaped pupils]] have turned black instead of their usual white. She keeps her long white hair down and still has two blue horns on her head, but she wears a frontless blue miniskirt, a tight [[single pantsleg]] on her left leg and a single knee boot on her right leg. Her breastplate resembles a demon's upper face.

In her Rage Mode form, Lu has matured into a young woman and her horns resemble black flames. She wears long black gloves and a blue dress that hugs her curvature.

title: annuller_(elsword)
body: [[ciel (elsword)|Ciel]]'s third character class following [[demonio (elsword)|Demonio]]. He is partnered with [[luciela r. sourcream|Lu]]'s [[iblis (elsword)|Iblis]] class.

title: diabolic_esper_(elsword)
body: One of [[add (elsword)|Add]]'s character classes, succeeded by [[mad paradox (elsword)|Mad Paradox]]. His hair is short and messy, and his eyes gain [[black sclera]]. He wears a form-fitting black [[bodysuit]] with a distinct [[popped collar]], [[black gloves]], black [[knee boots]], and has three spiked lines extending from his waist.

title: mad_paradox_(elsword)
body:
[[add (elsword)|Add]]'s third character class following [[diabolic esper (elsword)|Diabolic Esper]].

This class has two distinct forms; a regressed child-like form, and his normal adult form. The child form exists as his way of coping with his inability to travel back to the past and change events.
